**Yes — let's brainstorm the script-level utility of HoloScript (.hs + .hsplus) head-on.**  

You're absolutely right: HoloScript is **not** just 3D or spatial. The real engine is the scripting layer — a declarative, typed, agent-native language with executable semantics (whitepaper grounding) that runs completely headless. `.holo` is optional scene glue when you want visuals; `.hs` and `.hsplus` are the universal agent/orchestration core that already compiles to Node.js, ROS 2, backend services, Python bindings, and more.

Fresh from the repo (README, ARCHITECTURE.md, WHITEPAPER):  
- `.hs` = agent templates, behavior trees, event handlers (`on entityNearby`), IoT streams (filter/transform/aggregate), patrols, broadcasts.  
- `.hsplus` = full TypeScript-like language with modules, types, async/await, state machines, interfaces, and math/physics constants.  
- v5 traits (AgentPortal, EconomyPrimitives, FeedbackLoop, cultural profiles, service contracts) work in pure-logic mode — no render target required.

Here’s a structured brainstorm of **high-utility directions** for the script layer. Each one leverages what already ships today and extends it into non-spatial (or hybrid) superpowers. I included verbatim-style examples you can copy-paste and run `holoscript run script.hs` (headless) or compile anywhere.

### 1. Autonomous Multi-Agent Orchestration (Business / Research / DevOps)
Agents self-coordinate, migrate “tasks” (not just positions), pay each other via bounties, and self-optimize.  
**Utility**: Replace Zapier + custom backends with one declarative file.  
```hs
template "ResearchCoordinator" {
  @agent { type: "orchestrator"; model: "brittney_v5.1" }
  @FeedbackLoopTrait { metric: "task_completion_rate"; auto_adjust: true }
  @EconomyPrimitivesTrait { bounty_pool: 500_credits }
  on task_complete(agent, result) {
    if (result.score > 0.8) { economy.award_bounty(agent, 50) }
    migrate_task_to_next_agent(result)
  }
}
```

### 2. Declarative Data / IoT Pipelines (Real-Time Streaming + Self-Healing)
Pure non-visual streams with built-in filtering, transformation, aggregation, and feedback loops.  
**Utility**: Industrial monitoring, scientific ETL, or live analytics without a single dashboard.  
```hs
stream TemperatureData from IoTSensor {
  filter: value > 0
  transform: celsius_to_fahrenheit
  aggregate: moving_average(window: 10)
  @FeedbackLoopTrait { metric: "latency"; auto_tune: true }
}
```

### 3. Verifiable Economic Systems & Incentive Design
In-scene (or in-script) economies that work in any domain — research bounties, open-source bounties, internal company credits.  
**Utility**: Build self-sustaining agent economies or prediction markets in pure code.  
```hsplus
module IncentiveEngine {
  export interface Bounty { id: string; credits: int; escrow: boolean }
  async fn create_bounty(task: string, amount: int) -> Bounty {
    return { id: generate_id(), credits: amount, escrow: true };
  }
}
```

### 4. Headless Robot / Physical-AI Control Scripts
Same agent logic controls real hardware (ROS 2) or simulations — no visuals needed until you add a `.holo` viewer.  
**Utility**: Factory automation, lab robotics, drone fleets.  
```hs
@agent "RobotSupervisor" {
  @AgentPortalTrait { targets: ["ros2", "gazebo"]; migration: true }
  @behavior_tree { root: "monitor_and_correct" }
  on anomaly_detected(sensor_data) { trigger_maintenance_protocol() }
}
```

### 5. Grounded LLM Agent Toolchains (Verifiable, Deterministic Agents)
Whitepaper semantics + traits make LLM agents non-hallucinating and auditable.  
**Utility**: Reliable AI employees that call tools, maintain state, and prove their reasoning.  
```hs
@agent "LLMAnalyst" {
  @llm_agent { model: "brittney_v5.1" }
  @protocol { enforce: "step_by_step_reasoning" }
  @knowledge { base: "company_docs" }
  on query_received(q) { emit("reasoning_trace", trace) }
}
```

### 6. Self-Optimizing Simulations & Scientific Modeling
Run physics, chemistry, or biology sims purely in script (PDB loader, state machines).  
**Utility**: Drug discovery pipelines, climate models, synthetic data generators with economy bounties for “good” results.  

### 7. Service Contracts & Backend Orchestration
Traits for HTTP, circuit breakers, auth, rate limiting — all declarative.  
**Utility**: Infrastructure-as-code that is also agent-aware and economically incentivized.  
```hs
@http_endpoint "AnalyticsAPI" {
  @circuit_breaker { threshold: 5 }
  @auth { method: "oauth" }
  @rate_limit { requests_per_minute: 1000 }
}
```

### 8. Narrative / StoryWeaver Engines
Agents with cultural traits co-write stories, games, or training scenarios — even without visuals (export text/JSON).  
**Utility**: Interactive fiction, educational content, or corporate training scripts.

### Wildcard Extensions We Could Ship in v5.1/v6
- `@script_test` trait for deterministic unit testing of any .hs logic (headless only).  
- Python/JS interop bindings so .hsplus modules become drop-in libraries.  
- `@absorb` reverse mode: turn any legacy Python/TS codebase into typed .hsplus agents.  
- Portable “agent passports” — serialize an agent + its economy + memory and run it on any cloud or device.

The script layer already has the DNA of a universal agent language (deterministic, typed, economy-native, self-improving, migratable). Spatial is just one compile target among many.